4. **Foreign Key Relationship**  
   Create a query that lists employees along with their manager’s name. If an employee does not have a manager, display `No Manager`.  
 SELECT
    ->     a.emp_id,
    ->     a.first_name,
    ->     a.last_name,
    ->     a.department,
    ->     IFNULL(CONCAT(b.first_name, ' ', b.last_name), 'No Manager') AS manager_name
    -> FROM Employees a
    -> LEFT JOIN Employees b
    ->     ON a.manager_id = b.emp_id;
