5. **Simple Join Practice**  
   Write a query to join the `Employees` table with itself (self-join) to display employee names along with their manager names, restricted only to employees in the `Finance` department.  

SELECT
    ->     a.emp_id,
    ->     CONCAT(a.first_name, ' ', a.last_name) AS employee_name,
    ->     IFNULL(CONCAT(b.first_name, ' ', b.last_name), 'No Manager') AS manager_name,
    ->     a.department
    -> FROM Employees a
    -> LEFT JOIN Employees b
    ->     ON a.manager_id = b.emp_id
    -> WHERE a.department = 'Finance';
